# Trivy ignore policy (Program 15 Phase 3). Rules:
#   - every entry carries the evidence for WHY it is ignored and an owner/date;
#   - entries are revisited when the referenced work item lands — an ignore
#     with a stale justification gets deleted, loudly breaking the scan.

# DS-0002 (HIGH): "Specify at least 1 USER command" — docker/postgres/Dockerfile.
# The official postgres entrypoint is DESIGNED to start as root and drop to
# the postgres user via gosu (first-boot initdb/chown needs root). Adding
# USER postgres changes first-boot init behavior for the babylon-pg image,
# which feeds the byte-identical qa:e2e-regression bundle — that change
# belongs to the postgis base-image bump batch (Program 15 Phase 3 protocol:
# bump proven by local byte-identical qa:e2e-regression), not to a lint fix.
# Added 2026-07-11; revisit with the postgis bump.
DS-0002
